            <title>[ELY-458] Attachment and resource scopes for HTTP auth API</title>
                <link>https://issues.jboss.org/browse/ELY-458</link>
                <project id="12315320" key="ELY">WildFly Elytron</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Add an API to provide access to attachment and resource scopes as follows:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Exchange/Request&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Connection&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Session&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Application&#8224;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;SSL Session&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Global/JVM&#8224;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Scopes marked with &#8224; can have access to resources as well.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Scopes should also optionally support the registration of notifications so that a mechanism can be informed about the destruction of a specific scope.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
